comment: Elaine bredehoft committed perjury on the Depp Vs heard trial and continued to spread lies on the behalf of Amber heard about Johnny Depp being an abuser when Johnny depp has been proved in  Virginia court of law to be innocent of all charges.   Elaine has shown in the last month to be an habitual liar  in the Johnny depp Vs amber heard case and will not accept defeat.   Elaine has also gone on a personal man hunt to discredit certain jurors that served on the Depp vs heard case.   Elaine bredehoft is not to fit to continue to practice law under these conditions.
commentable_entity.ask: Amber Heard & Elaine Bredehoft STOP Using Domestic Abuse Victims
commentable_entity.title: Amber Heard & Elaine Bredehoft STOP Using Domestic Abuse Victims
commentable_entity.description:
I am a woman and a survivor of domestic abuse and after watching the recent trial of Johnny Depp and Amber Heard I am offended and disgusted by the statements made by Amber Heard and her Attorney Elaine Bredehoft like;

"A major setback for women inside the courtroom and outside the courtroom because basically what this jury said was unless you pull out your cell phone and tape your spouse beating you you're out of luck"

and

"It sets back the clock to a time when a woman who spoke up and spoke out could be publicly shamed and humiliated. It sets back the idea that violence against women is to be taken seriously."

For anyone who actually watched this trial, you know this is simply untrue, and for these statements to be made is a complete disregard for the law and the evidence presented.

I can only speak for myself when I say these statements are offensive and I do not want Amber Heard or Elaine Bredehoft speaking for me or my horrible journey through that abuse.

I personally, after watching the entire trial, and seeing all of the evidence presented, do not believe Amber Herd and urge you, if you also do not believe, and are or have been a victim of domestic abuse, to sign this petition asking Amber Heard and her legal team to please stop representing the rest of us survivors and victims in their legal defense and statements.

You have disrespected all of us, men and women alike who have had to live this horror. You have outraged so many of us in this despicable display. Please just stop.

Speak for yourself, speak for your client, but DO NOT speak for those of us who have had to endure the pain and suffering of domestic abuse, you are NOT our voice!
